text: Hankasalmi is a municipality in Central Finland. As of January 2014, about 5,400 people lived there. Neighbouring municipalities are Kangasniemi, Konnevesi, Laukaa, Pieksämäki, Rautalampi and Toivakka. Most people speak Finland. Hankasalmi was established in 1872. == Other websites == * The official Hankasalmi page Category:Municipalities of Central Finland Category:1872 establishments in Europe Category:1870s establishments in Finland
